+## 5. AC allocation — **the plan's "start at AC-078" is UNSAFE**
+
+`plan-0.8.20.md` §3 states the ceiling is **AC-077** and that new ACs "continue from" it. Re-verification shows
+that is a **reserved-id collision**:
+
+- **AC-077 is a RESERVED PLACEHOLDER**, not a defined gate — `dev/acceptance.md:1286` reserves it for the
+  **IR-eval IR-1/IR-2** initiative ("no fabricated numbers"; thresholds all TBD).
+- **AC-078 is *conditionally* reserved to the same initiative** — `:1297`: *"+ AC-078… only if the consensus
+  splits the measure."* A naive `grep -o 'AC-[0-9]*' | tail` returns AC-078 from this prose and will mislead.
+- Highest **defined, non-reserved** AC is **AC-076** (`:1147`). AC-075/076 are landed.
+
+**Recommendation (HITL call):** 0.8.20 mints its ACs starting at **AC-079**, leaving AC-077/078 to IR-1/IR-2.
+
+**And mint few.** Per the locked-`acceptance.md` policy (`acceptance-md-locked-no-feature-acs`), requirements are
+tracked by **requirement id + TDD test name**, not per-feature ACs. R-20-E1…E8 and the Phase-2 reqs are tracked by
+the §4 test names above. Only genuinely gated surfaces mint an AC:
+
+| New AC | Covers | Mirrors |
+|---|---|---|
+| **AC-079** | Governed-surface delta (Phase-2 + erasure API) vs the conformance allowlist — **HITL-SIGNED**; `recovery_denylist` unchanged (stays five) | AC-074 |
+| **AC-080** | Erasure completeness at rest: post-erase, the body is absent from **every** row-owned projection **and** the `-wal` bytes (raw-table + raw-byte assertions) | new (R-20-E1/E5) |
+
+**AC-041 is UNCHANGED and must stay GREEN** — it tests only the REQ-054 five-name denylist; `erase_source` is not
+one of the five.
