+## 7. R-20-EU7 — what would actually prove the no-op basis
+
+**Claim to prove:** Pin A keeps `SearchHit.id` byte-identical, so no gold-remap / re-baseline is needed.
+
+**Proof obligation at Slice 40** (all three; any failure ⇒ bounded re-baseline):
+
+1. `IdSpace::to_prefixed()` remains byte-identical to the pre-0.8.19 `stable_id` for `l:`/`h:`/`p:` — assert on a
+   frozen fixture set, not by inspection.
+2. **Migration guard: rows transitioning `logical_id NULL → NOT NULL` == 0** (the pin's invariant, R-20-SUR).
+3. eu7 vector-stage recall at the Slice-40 tip is **statistically indistinguishable** from the Slice-0 baseline
+   (§8) — same N, same seeds, **same backend**.
+
+**Hard constraint — eu7 is a CPU same-backend gate.** See §8; a GPU-run eu7 number is **not comparable** to the
+recorded floor and must never be used as the basis.
+
+---
+
+## 8. eu7 baseline — backend constraint (verified, load-bearing)
+
+The HITL GPU mandate (`repo-must-use-gpu-for-eval-when-3090-room`) directs eval/embed work onto the 3090s when
+there is room. **It does not apply to the eu7 recall gate**, by that mandate's own fidelity caveat:
+
+| Backend | n=7667 vector-stage recall@10 | CI | vs 0.90 floor (one-sided `ci_hi >= floor`) |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| **CPU** (GA-signoff, `GA-signoff-eu7-remeasure-20260608T172804Z.json`) | **0.8960** | [0.8640, **0.9250**] | **PASS** |
+| **GPU** (0.8.14, `0.8.14-slice-20-eu7-gpu-run-20260705T205222Z.log:73`) | **0.8330** | [0.8010, **0.8640**] | **FAIL** |
+
+The GPU figure is a **cross-backend artifact**, not a regression (it is the TC-5 re-baseline driver, scheduled
+0.8.23). Running the 0.8.20 baseline on GPU would manufacture a false regression and could wrongly force a
+re-baseline. **The eu7 basis decision must be taken on CPU numbers only.**
+
+### 8.1 Harness defect found — the documented run command does not work
+
+`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs:85-86` documents:
+
+```text
+AGENT_LONG=1 cargo test -p fathomdb-engine --features default-embedder \
+  --test eu7_real_corpus_ac -- --nocapture
+```
+
+This **fails with exit 101** — the target also requires the **`operator`** feature:
+`error: target 'eu7_real_corpus_ac' in package 'fathomdb-engine' requires the features: 'operator'`.
+The working invocation is `--features default-embedder,operator`. Fix the docstring in Slice 5.
+
+### 8.2 Corpus is not reachable from a worktree
+
+`data/corpus-data/` is **gitignored** (`.gitignore:9`) and exists only in the primary checkout (2.1 GB). From a
+linked worktree `load_subset_or_skip` finds no corpus and the test **SKIPS** — printing `[skip]` and returning
+**exit 0**. Combined with §8.1 this is a double vacuous-green hazard: an unwary run reports success having
+measured nothing. Slice 40 must assert the harness actually ran (non-skip witness), not merely that it exited 0.
